# https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#ResearchInfrastructure> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/homepage> <https://www.emso-fr.org/> .
<https://www.emso-fr.org/> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/homepage> <https://www.emso-fr.org/fr> .
<https://www.emso-fr.org/fr> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#RegionalFacilityisledby> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Dominique_LEFEVRE> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#RegionalFacilityisledby> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Nadine_LANTERI> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#hasCountry> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#France> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#isManagedBy> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#CNRS> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#isManagedBy> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Ifremer> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "A infraestrutura de investigação EMSO-France, incluída no roteiro do MESR, coordena as iniciativas francesas sobre observatórios submarinos do programa europeu e promove a sua abertura a uma ampla gama de equipas e disciplinas. O envolvimento de França baseia-se na sua experiência em gestão de dados, inovação tecnológica e na seleção estratégica dos locais de implantação:\n                                    \n                                    o sítio dos Açores na dorsal médio-atlântica, na ZEE de Portugal,\n                                    o sítio do Mar da Ligúria, a leste na encosta de Nice e a oeste na zona profunda do talude continental, ligado ao telescópio de neutrinos do IN2P3,\n                                    o sítio do Mar de Mármara ao longo da falha norte da Anatólia,\n                                    o sítio de teste no Mar de Iroise, inicialmente ao largo de Molène, atualmente em relocalização para o porto de Brest."@pt .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "EMSO-France Research Infrastructure, included in the MESR roadmap, coordinates French initiatives on underwater observatories within the European programme and promotes their openness to a wide range of teams and disciplines. France’s involvement is driven by its expertise in data management, technological innovation, and the strategic selection of observatory deployment sites:\n                                    \n                                    the Azores site on the Mid-Atlantic Ridge, within Portugal’s EEZ,\n                                    the Ligurian Sea site, east on the Nice slope and west in the deep continental margin area, linked to the IN2P3 neutrino telescope,\n                                    the Marmara Sea site along the North Anatolian Fault,\n                                    the Iroise Sea test site, initially located offshore Molène, currently being relocated to Brest harbour."@en .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "EMSO-France forskningsinfrastruktur, inkludert i MESR sin veikart, koordinerer franske initiativer for undervannsobservatorier innen det europeiske programmet og fremmer deres åpning for et bredt spekter av team og fagområder. Frankrikes engasjement bygger på kompetanse innen databehandling, teknologisk innovasjon og strategisk valg av lokaliteter:\n                                    \n                                    Azorene på den midtatlantiske ryggen, innenfor Portugals økonomiske sone,\n                                    det liguriske hav, øst ved Nice-skråningen og vest i den dype kontinentalskråningen, knyttet til IN2P3s nøytrinoteleskop,\n                                    Marmarahavet langs den nordanatoliske forkastningen,\n                                    teststedet i Iroisehavet, opprinnelig utenfor Molène, nå under relokalisering til Brest havn."@no .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Infrastructura de cercetare EMSO-France, inclusă în foaia de parcurs MESR, coordonează inițiativele franceze privind observatoarele submarine din programul european și promovează deschiderea acestora către o gamă largă de echipe și discipline. Implicarea Franței se bazează pe expertiza în gestionarea datelor, inovare tehnologică și selecția strategică a locațiilor:\n                                    \n                                    situl Azorelor pe dorsala medio-atlantică, în ZEE Portugaliei,\n                                    sitului Mării Ligurice, la est pe panta de la Nisa și la vest în zona adâncă a taluzului continental, legat de telescopul de neutrini IN2P3,\n                                    sitului Mării Marmara pe falia nord-anatoliană,\n                                    situl de testare din Marea Iroise, inițial în largul Molène, în curs de relocare în portul Brest."@ro .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "La Infraestructura de Investigación EMSO-France, incluida en la hoja de ruta del MESR, coordina las iniciativas francesas sobre observatorios submarinos del programa europeo y promueve su apertura a un amplio abanico de equipos y disciplinas. La implicación de Francia se basa en su experiencia en gestión de datos, innovación tecnológica y en la elección estratégica de los emplazamientos de los observatorios:\n                                    \n                                    el sitio de las Azores en la dorsal mesoatlántica, dentro de la ZEE de Portugal,\n                                    el sitio del mar de Liguria, al este en la pendiente de Niza y al oeste en la zona profunda del margen continental, vinculado al telescopio de neutrinos del IN2P3,\n                                    el sitio del mar de Mármara en la falla de Anatolia del Norte,\n                                    el sitio de ensayo en el mar de Iroise, inicialmente frente a Molène, actualmente en proceso de traslado a la rada de Brest."@es .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "L’infrastructure de recherche EMSO-France, inscrite dans la feuille de route du MESR, coordonne les initiatives françaises sur les observatoires sous-marins du programme européen et favorise leur ouverture à un large éventail d’équipes et de disciplines. L’engagement de la France repose sur son expertise en gestion de données, en innovation technologique et sur le choix stratégique des sites d’implantation des observatoires :\n                                    \n                                    le site des Açores sur la dorsale médio-atlantique, dans la ZEE du Portugal,\n                                    le site de la mer Ligure, à l’est sur la pente de Nice et à l’ouest dans la zone profonde du talus continental, en lien avec le télescope à neutrinos de l’IN2P3,\n                                    le site de la mer de Marmara sur la faille nord-anatolienne,\n                                    le site d’essai en mer d’Iroise, initialement au large de Molène, en cours de relocalisation en rade de Brest."@fr .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "L’infrastruttura di ricerca EMSO-France, inclusa nella roadmap del MESR, coordina le iniziative francesi sugli osservatori sottomarini del programma europeo e ne promuove l’apertura a un’ampia gamma di team e discipline. Il coinvolgimento della Francia si basa sulla sua esperienza nella gestione dei dati, nell’innovazione tecnologica e nella selezione strategica dei siti di installazione:\n                                    \n                                    il sito delle Azzorre sulla dorsale medio-atlantica, nella ZEE del Portogallo,\n                                    il sito del Mar Ligure, a est sulla scarpata di Nizza e a ovest nella zona profonda del margine continentale, collegato al telescopio a neutrini dell’IN2P3,\n                                    il sito del Mar di Marmara lungo la faglia nord-anatolica,\n                                    il sito di prova nel mare d’Iroise, inizialmente al largo di Molène, attualmente in fase di trasferimento nel porto di Brest."@it .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Η Ερευνητική Υποδομή EMSO-France, ενταγμένη στον οδικό χάρτη του MESR, συντονίζει τις γαλλικές πρωτοβουλίες για τα υποθαλάσσια παρατηρητήρια του ευρωπαϊκού προγράμματος και προωθεί το άνοιγμά τους σε όσο το δυνατόν περισσότερες ομάδες και επιστημονικά πεδία. Η συμμετοχή της Γαλλίας βασίζεται στον ρόλο της στη διαχείριση δεδομένων, στην τεχνολογική καινοτομία και στην επιλογή των θέσεων εγκατάστασης των παρατηρητηρίων:\n\n                                    τοποθεσία των Αζορών στη Μεσο-Ατλαντική Ράχη, εντός της ΑΟΖ της Πορτογαλίας,\n                                    τοποθεσία της Λιγυρίας Θάλασσας, ανατολικά στην πλαγιά της Νίκαιας και στη βαθιά ζώνη του ηπειρωτικού περιθωρίου, δυτικά, σε σύνδεση με το τηλεσκόπιο νετρίνων του IN2P3,\n                                    τοποθεσία της Θάλασσας του Μαρμαρά πάνω στο ρήγμα της Βόρειας Ανατολίας,\n                                    ο δοκιμαστικός χώρος στη Θάλασσα της Ιρουάζ, αρχικά εγκατεστημένος ανοικτά της Molène, σε διαδικασία μετεγκατάστασης στον όρμο της Βρέστης."@el .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-France> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> <https://ror.org/0312sjw67> .
